					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12366640#post-4337313</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12366640/scp-4247#post-4337313</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 22 Aug 2019 08:01:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Petrograd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>455145</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Not big on this one. The framing device &quot;causing&quot; this to be in kind of a bland and direct-exposition-riddled tone neither made made a particularly striking impression nor stopped it from being&#8230; well, bland and direct-exposition-riddled.</p> <p>Edit: We're also talking about a couple genres of articles (affect the text, fictonauts, and trapped-in-an-SCP) that all have some real standouts. For just one example with similar elements, compare <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/to-be-noir-not-to-be">To Be Noir Not To Be</a>. The core story you tell isn't a bad idea, but&#8230;</p> <p>That's not the way to make me care about a story, and definitely not the way to make me care about Bob.<br /> -1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
